    {
      "paragraph_name": "RECEIVE-PAULST-SCREEN",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph receives data from the COPAU0A screen. It executes a CICS RECEIVE command to receive the map `COPAU0A` from mapset `COPAU00` into the input map `COPAU0AI`. The `RESP` and `RESP2` options are used to capture the CICS response codes in `WS-RESP-CD` and `WS-REAS-CD`, respectively. This paragraph retrieves the data entered by the user on the screen. The received data will be used in subsequent processing steps. Error handling is performed by checking the `WS-RESP-CD` and `WS-REAS-CD` fields after the RECEIVE command. The paragraph's primary purpose is to get input from the user via the CICS screen.",
