    {
      "paragraph_name": "GETCARDXREF-BYACCT",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph retrieves the card cross-reference record from the `CARDXREF` file based on the account ID. It moves the account ID (`WS-ACCT-ID`) to the key field (`WS-CARD-RID-ACCT-ID-X`). It then executes a CICS READ command to read the record from the `CARDXREF` file using the alternate index `ACCTID`. If the read is successful (`DFHRESP(NORMAL)`), it moves the customer ID and card number from the cross-reference record to `CDEMO-CUST-ID` and `CDEMO-CARD-NUM`, respectively. If the record is not found (`DFHRESP(NOTFND)`), it constructs an error message and calls `SEND-PAULST-SCREEN` to display the message. If any other error occurs, it sets an error flag (`WS-ERR-FLG`), constructs an error message, and calls `SEND-PAULST-SCREEN` to display the message. This paragraph handles the retrieval of the card cross-reference data and displays an error message if the record is not found or if a system error occurs. The file name is stored in `WS-CARDXREFNAME-ACCT-PATH`.",
