    {
      "paragraph_name": "SCHEDULE-PSB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "The SCHEDULE-PSB paragraph is responsible for scheduling a Program Specification Block (PSB) within an IMS environment. It first attempts to schedule the PSB using the `EXEC DLI SCHD` command, specifying the PSB name and disabling Dhabend abend processing (lines 3-6). The DIBSTAT value is moved to IMS-RETURN-CODE for checking the status of the scheduling. If the PSB has been scheduled more than once (PSB-SCHEDULED-MORE-THAN-ONCE), it terminates the current PSB and schedules it again (lines 8-17). If the scheduling is successful (STATUS-OK), the IMS-PSB-SCHD flag is set to TRUE (lines 18-19). If the scheduling fails, an error flag (WS-ERR-FLG) is set to 'Y', an error message is constructed including the IMS-RETURN-CODE, and the message is stored in WS-MESSAGE (lines 21-28). Finally, it moves -1 to ACCTIDL of COPAU0AI and calls the SEND-PAULST-SCREEN program to display the error message (lines 29-30).",
